      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and relative hemolysis (RH) predicted by CFD must agree with experimental measurements within 15% across all 5 operating points.",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison of CFD-predicted NIH against in-vitro measurements at all 5 operating points. Mean absolute error 12.3%, maximum error 14.7% at the 3500 RPM / 2.5 L/min operating point. All comparisons within the 15% acceptance criterion. RH < 1.0 at all points relative to predicate device."
    },
    {
