    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required gradation levels for MRL 2. The 6 not-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3. CFD predictions of relative hemolysis index satisfy RH < 1.0 acceptance criterion at all 5 operating points. The hemolysis modeling methodology referenced in the primary methods publication (doi:10.1016/j.ymeth.2024.03.003) underpins the power-law damage accumulation approach used throughout this assessment. Overall credibility package supports Accepted decision for use of CFD hemolysis predictions in the Class II CPB device regulatory submission.",
